(387, NULL, 'Turtwig', '387.png', 'Tiny Leaf Pokemon', 'Grass', NULL, 'This Pokemon becomes more energetic the more sunlight there is. The part resembling a shell is similar to silt and is slightly damp and warm to the touch.'),
(388, NULL, 'Grotle', '388.png', 'Grove Pokemon', 'Grass', NULL, 'Appears where there is clean spring water. The fruit that grows on the shrubs on its shell is sweet, nutritious, and truly delicious.'),
(389, NULL, 'Torterra', '389.png', 'Continent Pokemon', 'Grass', 'Ground', 'This remarkable, large-bodied Pokemon would serve beautifully as borrowed scenery for a garden, and its strength is peerless. Torterra roams the wilderness in search of clean water.'),
(390, NULL, 'Chimchar', '390.png', 'Chimp Pokemon', 'Fire', NULL, 'It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.'),
(391, NULL, 'Monferno', '391.png', 'Playful Pokemon', 'Fire', 'Fighting', 'The deeper the blue on its face, the more powerful it will grow to become. It leaps about every which way and lands powerful blows against its opponents with the flame on its tail.'),
(392, NULL, 'Infernape', '392.png', 'Flame Pokemon', 'Fire', 'Fighting', 'A tall, hardy Pokemon with a dazzling appearance. It shrouds itself in flame and battles as if engaged in dance—truly a sight to behold.'),
(393, NULL, 'Piplup', '393.png', 'Penguin Pokemon', 'Water', NULL, 'Prefers cold climes and appears along coasts. It''s an adorable little thing—as cute as any child—but it''s also prideful, unwilling to accept handouts from people.'),
(394, NULL, 'Prinplup', '394.png', 'Penguin Pokemon', 'Water', NULL, 'It swims gracefully through the frigid sea and sings with a voice like the roaring tide. It has powerful, sturdy wings and dignity to match.'),
(395, NULL, 'Empoleon', '395.png', 'Emperor Pokemon', 'Water', 'Steel', 'It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.'),
(396, NULL, 'Starly', '396.png', 'Starling Pokemon', 'Normal', 'Flying', 'Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.'),
(397, NULL, 'Staravia', '397.png', 'Starling Pokemon', 'Normal', 'Flying', 'Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.'),
(398, NULL, 'Staraptor', '398.png', 'Predator Pokemon', 'Normal', 'Flying', 'When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.'),
(399, NULL, 'Bidoof', '399.png', 'Plump Mouse Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'Bidoof has an unsophisticated face and is rarely flustered by anything. There have been incidents involving Bidoof sauntering into villages and gnawing on the houses without a single care.'),
(400, NULL, 'Bibarel', '400.png', 'Beaver Pokemon', 'Normal', 'Water', 'Bibarel fur repels water and is also a fantastic material for heat retention. These Pokemon create dams on rivers to live in.'),
(401, NULL, 'Kricketot', '401.png', 'Cricket Pokemon', 'Bug', NULL, 'Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.'),
(402, NULL, 'Kricketune', '402.png', 'Cricket Pokemon', 'Bug', NULL, 'By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its belly, it produces a captivating sound.'),
(403, NULL, 'Shinx', '403.png', 'Flash Pokemon', 'Electric', NULL, 'The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.'),
(404, NULL, 'Luxio', '404.png', 'Spark Pokemon', 'Electric', NULL, 'Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.'),
(405, NULL, 'Luxray', '405.png', 'Gleam Eyes Pokemon', 'Electric', NULL, 'It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.'),
(406, NULL, 'Budew', '406.png', 'Bud Pokemon', 'Grass', 'Poison', 'When the sun''s light strengthens, the bud atop this Pokemon''s head opens. This is a sign to the people that the harsh winter is over, and the season of budding has begun.'),
(407, NULL, 'Roserade', '407.png', 'Bouquet Pokemon', 'Grass', 'Poison', 'Hidden within the bouquet on each hand are thorned whips loaded with virulent poison. Roserade moves gracefully as it corners its prey and mercilessly lashes them with its whips.'),
(408, NULL, 'Cranidos', '408.png', 'Head Butt Pokemon', 'Rock', NULL, 'An incredibly rare sight. They duel each other by ramming their heads together, and the resulting sound echoes throughout the area like the pealing of a bell.'),
(409, NULL, 'Rampardos', '409.png', 'Head Butt Pokemon', 'Rock', NULL, 'Very little is known about its biology. Can knock down massive trees by smashing its beautiful, pearl-like crown against them.'),
(410, NULL, 'Shieldon', '410.png', 'Shield Pokemon', 'Rock', 'Steel', 'Much remains unknown about this Pokemon, as few have ever seen it. However, we know that it is calm and dislikes conflict, and it enjoys polishing its face against trees and rocks.'),
(411, NULL, 'Bastiodon', '411.png', 'Shield Pokemon', 'Rock', 'Steel', 'Its face is sturdy—as strong as diamond—and this hardness offers a very stable defense. Much about this species is still unknown, such as its natural habitat.'),
(412, NULL, 'Burmy', '412.png', 'Bagworm Pokemon', 'Bug', NULL, 'If its cloak is even slightly damaged, Burmy will immediately repair it with whatever is close at hand. The Pokemon within the cloak is scrawny and vulnerable to the cold.'),
(413, NULL, 'Wormadam', '413.png', 'Bagworm Pokemon', 'Bug', 'Grass', 'The cloak—fashioned from plant matter—has merged with the Pokemon and is now part of the body, like fur or skin. I suspect this fusion is an effect of the energy involved in evolution.'),
(414, NULL, 'Mothim', '414.png', 'Moth Pokemon', 'Bug', 'Flying', 'Scatters steel-colored scales as it flaps its wings. Despite being observed feeding primarily on the nectar of flowers, Mothim is not often seen around flower gardens.'),
(415, NULL, 'Combee', '415.png', 'Tiny Bee Pokemon', 'Bug', 'Flying', 'The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers nectar from flowers to please Vespiquen.'),
(416, NULL, 'Vespiquen', '416.png', 'Beehive Pokemon', 'Bug', 'Flying', 'It houses its colony in cells in its body and releases various pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding.'),
(417, NULL, 'Pachirisu', '417.png', 'EleSquirrel Pokemon', 'Electric', NULL, 'A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.'),
(418, NULL, 'Buizel', '418.png', 'Sea Weasel Pokemon', 'Water', NULL, 'It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.'),
(419, NULL, 'Floatzel', '419.png', 'Sea Weasel Pokemon', 'Water', NULL, 'With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.'),
(420, NULL, 'Cherubi', '420.png', 'Cherry Pokemon', 'Grass', NULL, 'Once the fruit growing alongside the main body is large and plump, Cherubi will use the nutrients within to evolve. The fruit then detaches, becoming nourishment for other creatures.'),
(421, NULL, 'Cherrim', '421.png', 'Blossom Pokemon', 'Grass', NULL, 'It is docile as a bud and turns cheerful when it blooms. It folds back into a bud if sunlight wanes.'),
(422, NULL, 'Shellos', '422.png', 'Sea Slug Pokemon', 'Water', NULL, 'Found in abundance on seashores bordering warm waters. Shellos are unexpectedly friendly and will crawl toward any person they see. Take care not to get coated in mucus!'),
(423, NULL, 'Gastrodon', '423.png', 'Sea Slug Pokemon', 'Water', 'Ground', 'Eats beach sand for nourishment. Should one Gastrodon encounter another of a different color, a fierce battle will inevitably ensue.'),
(424, NULL, 'Ambipom', '424.png', 'Long Tail Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'To affirm their kinship, members of this species will form a ring by linking their newly doubled tails together. On rare occasions, humans have been accepted into such rings.'),
(425, NULL, 'Drifloon', '425.png', 'Balloon Pokemon', 'Ghost', 'Flying', 'Said to lure away young children and carry them off to the afterlife. Some whisper that Drifloon are formed of reincarnated human souls, but these rumors are as yet unconfirmed.'),
(426, NULL, 'Drifblim', '426.png', 'Blimp Pokemon', 'Ghost', 'Flying', 'It can generate and release gas within its body. That''s how it can control the altitude of its drift.'),
(427, NULL, 'Buneary', '427.png', 'Rabbit Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.'),
(428, NULL, 'Lopunny', '428.png', 'Rabbit Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'Its fur is warm and yet remarkably light. This Pokemon kicks as though it were a master of karate, driving back its opponents with ease.'),
(429, NULL, 'Mismagius', '429.png', 'Magical Pokemon', 'Ghost', NULL, 'Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.'),
(430, NULL, 'Honchkrow', '430.png', 'Big Boss Pokemon', 'Dark', 'Flying', 'It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.'),
(431, NULL, 'Glameow', '431.png', 'Catty Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'Bewitches humans with its helical tail and piercing gaze. Its hidden claws are quite sharp as well, making this Pokemon an exceedingly tricky opponent if antagonized.'),
(432, NULL, 'Purugly', '432.png', 'Tiger Cat Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.'),
(433, NULL, 'Chingling', '433.png', 'Bell Pokemon', 'Psychic', NULL, 'This Pokemon gave me an excruciating headache when it seemingly cried out without making a sound. Perhaps there are some sounds that the human ear is simply incapable of hearing.'),
(434, NULL, 'Stunky', '434.png', 'Skunk Pokemon', 'Poison', 'Dark', 'It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokemon away.'),
(435, NULL, 'Skuntank', '435.png', 'Skunk Pokemon', 'Poison', 'Dark', 'It attacks by spraying a repugnant fluid from its tail, but the stench dulls after a few squirts.'),
(436, NULL, 'Bronzor', '436.png', 'Bronze Pokemon', 'Steel', 'Psychic', 'They are found in ancient tombs. The patterns on their backs are said to be imbued with mysterious power.'),
(437, NULL, 'Bronzong', '437.png', 'Bronze Bell Pokemon', 'Steel', 'Psychic', 'It brought rains by opening portals to another world. It was revered as a bringer of plentiful harvests.'),
(438, NULL, 'Bonsly', '438.png', 'Bonsai Pokemon', 'Rock', NULL, 'From its eyes, it can expel excess moisture from its body. This liquid is similar in composition to human sweat.'),
(439, NULL, 'Mime Jr.', '439.png', 'Mime Pokemon', 'Psychic', 'Fairy', 'It likes places where people gather. It mimics foes to confuse them, then makes its getaway.'),
(440, NULL, 'Happiny', '440.png', 'Playhouse Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It''s bothered by how curly its hair looks.'),
(441, NULL, 'Chatot', '441.png', 'Music Note Pokemon', 'Normal', 'Flying', 'A versatile performer skilled in the imitation of human speech. It is said that older, more experienced Chatot can even understand the meaning of the words they mimic.'),
(442, NULL, 'Spiritomb', '442.png', 'Forbidden Pokemon', 'Ghost', 'Dark', 'It was formed by uniting 108 spirits. It has been bound to the Odd Keystone to keep it from doing any mischief.'),
(443, NULL, 'Gible', '443.png', 'Land Shark Pokemon', 'Dragon', 'Ground', 'It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.'),
(444, NULL, 'Gabite', '444.png', 'Cave Pokemon', 'Dragon', 'Ground', 'In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.'),
(445, NULL, 'Garchomp', '445.png', 'Mach Pokemon', 'Dragon', 'Ground', 'It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.'),
(446, NULL, 'Munchlax', '446.png', 'Big Eater Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing it whole with almost no chewing.'),
(447, NULL, 'Riolu', '447.png', 'Emanation Pokemon', 'Fighting', NULL, 'They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.'),
(448, NULL, 'Lucario', '448.png', 'Aura Pokemon', 'Fighting', 'Steel', 'It''s said that no foe can remain invisible to Lucario, since it can detect auras—even those of foes it could not otherwise see.'),
(449, NULL, 'Hippopotas', '449.png', 'Hippo Pokemon', 'Ground', NULL, 'It shuts its nostrils tight, then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.'),
(450, NULL, 'Hippowdon', '450.png', 'Heavyweight Pokemon', 'Ground', NULL, 'It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth agape as a display of its strength.'),
(451, NULL, 'Skorupi', '451.png', 'Scorpion Pokemon', 'Poison', 'Bug', 'Its claws are not only razor-sharp but poisonous, making Skorupi a highly dangerous Pokemon. It seems to be weakened by cold temperatures, however.'),
(452, NULL, 'Drapion', '452.png', 'Ogre Scorp Pokemon', 'Poison', 'Dark', 'Has a brutish, ferocious temperament. With immense strength and a sturdy shell off which swords will bounce, it rampages about and wreaks havoc.'),
(453, NULL, 'Croagunk', '453.png', 'Toxic Mouth Pokemon', 'Poison', 'Fighting', 'Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.'),
(454, NULL, 'Toxicroak', '454.png', 'Toxic Mouth Pokemon', 'Poison', 'Fighting', 'Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes, it weaves its flexible body in close, then lunges out with its poisonous claws.'),
(455, NULL, 'Carnivine', '455.png', 'Bug Catcher Pokemon', 'Grass', NULL, 'Though this is a plant Pokemon, it has a gluttonous and unruly temperament. Carnivine attacks its prey with its cavernous maw wide open.'),
(456, NULL, 'Finneon', '456.png', 'Wing Fish Pokemon', 'Water', NULL, 'The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.'),
(457, NULL, 'Lumineon', '457.png', 'Neon Pokemon', 'Water', NULL, 'With its shining light, it lures its prey close. However, the light also happens to attract ferocious fish Pokemon—its natural predators.'),
(458, NULL, 'Mantyke', '458.png', 'Kite Pokemon', 'Water', 'Flying', 'Though ball-like in shape, this Pokemon is a proficient swimmer. I have discovered that if a Mantyke spends much time with schools of Remoraid, it will eventually achieve evolution.'),
(459, NULL, 'Snover', '459.png', 'Frost Tree Pokemon', 'Grass', 'Ice', 'During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain''s lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.'),
(460, NULL, 'Abomasnow', '460.png', 'Frost Tree Pokemon', 'Grass', 'Ice', 'It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.'),
(461, NULL, 'Weavile', '461.png', 'Sharp Claw Pokemon', 'Dark', 'Ice', 'They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.'),
(462, NULL, 'Magnezone', '462.png', 'Magnet Area Pokemon', 'Electric', 'Steel', 'Exposure to a special magnetic field changed Magneton''s molecular structure, turning it into Magnezone.'),
(463, NULL, 'Lickilicky', '463.png', 'Licking Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'Its tongue can extend and contract freely, and it is capable of reaching lengths over 10 times Lickilicky''s height. Beware of the saliva, as it contains corrosive elements.'),
(464, NULL, 'Rhyperior', '464.png', 'Drill Pokemon', 'Ground', 'Rock', 'It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. On rare occasions, the Pokemon even shoots out Geodude.'),
(465, NULL, 'Tangrowth', '465.png', 'Vine Pokemon', 'Grass', NULL, 'Draped with long vines, it resembles a shrub in appearance. It swings bundles of vines as though they were arms, wrapping them around prey to ensnare them.'),
(466, NULL, 'Electivire', '466.png', 'Thunderbolt Pokemon', 'Electric', NULL, 'Its evolution was induced by an unusual item, and its electrical output rises along with its heart rate. From its tails, it can unleash an electric current measuring 20,000 volts.'),
(467, NULL, 'Magmortar', '467.png', 'Blast Pokemon', 'Fire', NULL, 'Use of a strange item caused this Pokemon to evolve. Fireballs launched from the ends of its tubelike arms are hot enough to melt an iron pot in an instant.'),
(468, NULL, 'Togekiss', '468.png', 'Jubilee Pokemon', 'Fairy', 'Flying', 'It will never appear where there is strife. Sightings of this Pokemon have recently become rare.'),
(469, NULL, 'Yanmega', '469.png', 'Ogre Darner Pokemon', 'Bug', 'Flying', 'It prefers to battle by biting apart foes'' heads instantly while flying by at high speed.'),
(470, NULL, 'Leafeon', '470.png', 'Verdant Pokemon', 'Grass', NULL, 'The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.'),
(471, NULL, 'Glaceon', '471.png', 'Fresh Snow Pokemon', 'Ice', NULL, 'It can control its body temperature at will. This enables it to freeze the moisture in the atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.'),
(472, NULL, 'Gliscor', '472.png', 'Fang Scorp Pokemon', 'Ground', 'Flying', 'It glides soundlessly on pitch-black wings and sinks sharp fangs into the throat of its prey. It takes on a look of satisfaction once it has entirely drained its prey of blood.'),
(473, NULL, 'Mamoswine', '473.png', 'Twin Tusk Pokemon', 'Ice', 'Ground', 'Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The ice age is over and the climate has warmed, so this Pokemon''s population has thinned.'),
(474, NULL, 'Porygon-Z', '474.png', 'Virtual Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'Additional software was installed to make it an even better Pokemon. It began acting oddly, however.'),
(475, NULL, 'Gallade', '475.png', 'Blade Pokemon', 'Psychic', 'Fighting', 'When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.'),
(476, NULL, 'Probopass', '476.png', 'Compass Pokemon', 'Rock', 'Steel', 'It is able to emit powerful magnetism, allowing it control over the iron sand that forms its luscious mustache. Using this iron sand, Probopass forms hard stones with which it smites its prey.'),
(477, NULL, 'Dusknoir', '477.png', 'Gripper Pokemon', 'Ghost', NULL, 'Comes to those whose lives have come to an end and escorts their souls to the afterlife. Known to mistakenly take the souls of those who yet have life left in them, albeit rarely.'),
(478, NULL, 'Froslass', '478.png', 'Snow Land Pokemon', 'Ice', 'Ghost', 'It spits out cold air of nearly -60 degrees Fahrenheit to freeze its quarry. It brings frozen prey back to its lair and neatly lines them up.'),
(479, NULL, 'Rotom', '479.png', 'Plasma Pokemon', 'Electric', 'Ghost', 'Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.'),
(480, NULL, 'Uxie', '480.png', 'Knowledge Pokemon', 'Psychic', NULL, 'A Pokemon feared but also respected for stealing away the memories of evildoers. I have found records that suggest Uxie holds dominion over knowledge.'),
(481, NULL, 'Mesprit', '481.png', 'Emotion Pokemon', 'Psychic', NULL, 'Known as the Being of Emotion. In legend, this Pokemon was feared, as any who showed disrespect would have their emotions thrown into disarray.'),
(482, NULL, 'Azelf', '482.png', 'Willpower Pokemon', 'Psychic', NULL, 'The dreaded Being of Willpower. Legends tell of this Pokemon manipulating the will of its adversaries and turning them into puppets of its own.'),
(483, NULL, 'Dialga', '483.png', 'Temporal Pokemon', 'Steel', 'Dragon', 'This Pokemon is spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.'),
(484, NULL, 'Palkia', '484.png', 'Spatial Pokemon', 'Water', 'Dragon', 'It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. Palkia appears in mythology.'),
(485, NULL, 'Heatran', '485.png', 'Lava Dome Pokemon', 'Fire', 'Steel', 'It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.'),
(486, NULL, 'Regigigas', '486.png', 'Colossal Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'It''s said that Regigigas created other Pokemon from many different materials before it moved the continents to where they are today.'),
(487, NULL, 'Giratina', '487.png', 'Renegade Pokemon', 'Ghost', 'Dragon', 'A Pokemon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.'),
(488, NULL, 'Cresselia', '488.png', 'Lunar Pokemon', 'Psychic', NULL, 'When it flies, it releases shiny particles from its veil-like wings. It is said to represent the crescent moon.'),
(489, NULL, 'Phione', '489.png', 'Sea Drifter Pokemon', 'Water', NULL, 'A Pokemon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.'),
(490, NULL, 'Manaphy', '490.png', 'Seafaring Pokemon', 'Water', NULL, 'Water makes up 80 percent of its body. This Pokemon is easily affected by its environment.'),
(491, NULL, 'Darkrai', '491.png', 'Pitch-Black Pokemon', 'Dark', NULL, 'Folklore has it that on moonless nights, this Pokemon will make people see horrific nightmares.'),
(492, NULL, 'Shaymin', '492.png', 'Gratitude Pokemon', 'Grass', NULL, 'It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.'),
(493, NULL, 'Arceus', '493.png', 'Alpha Pokemon', 'Normal', NULL, 'It is told in mythology that this Pokemon was the first Pokemon born before the universe even existed.'),
